==English==

===Noun===
'''facebook'''  (''plural:'' '''[[facebooks]]''')

# A facebook is a [[book]] that is made up of [[photographs]] of individuals along with their names. Facebooks are often published as an orientation handout at the start of the academic year by the administrations of [[college]]s and [[university|universities]], with the intention of helping [[students]], [[faculty]], and [[staff]] to get to know each other better.
#:''When will the facebooks be printed?''

===Related terms===
A facebook may be contrasted with a [[yearbook]], which is traditionally published at the end of the academic year and usually includes details about various aspects of the preceding year, along with the sort of content one would find in a facebook.

